tant mediation between the old forms of knowledge and the new.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Mai 2022) 0aNatural history museumszEuropexHistory. 0aNatural history museumszItalyxHistory. 0aScience museumszEuropexHistory. 0aScience museumszItalyxHistory. 7aHISTORY / Europe / General.2bisacsh  a1500s.  aacademic.  aancient world.  aarchival.  aarchives.  aart museum.  abaroque.  abiology.  aeuropean history.  aexperiment.  ahumanist.  alife science.  amodern world.  amuseum.  anatural history museum.  anatural history.  anatural world.  areconstruction.  areligion.  areligious studies.  arenaissance.  ascholarly.  ascience.  ascientific revolution.  auniversity.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Package Archive Pre-2000z978311063534840uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/978052091778140uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520917781423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520917781/original  a978-3-11-063534-8  University of California Press Package Archive Pre-2000b2000  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles